Here is the full **testsmells.org 19-smell academic catalog** audit of `UserRepositoryIntegrationTests.cs`, with integration-test calibration applied.

---

## Summary Dashboard

| Severity | Smell Count | Affected Tests |
|----------|-------------|----------------|
| High     | 3           | 3              |
| Medium   | 1           | 1              |
| Low      | 0           | 0              |
| **Total**| **4**       | **4**          |

All 19 catalog smells were checked. 15 smells came back clean.

---

## Findings by Severity

### 🔴 HIGH — Sleepy Test

**File:** `UserRepositoryIntegrationTests.cs` **Method:** `NotifyOnInsert_SendsEventAfterDelay` (line 87)

```csharp
Thread.Sleep(3000); // ← fixed 3-second wait
```

**Integration calibration:** Even in integration tests, a hard `Thread.Sleep` is a smell. It makes the suite slow and can cause false failures on slow machines. Use a polling/retry loop or `TaskCompletionSource` instead.

**Fix:**
```csharp
// Poll with timeout instead of sleeping
var sw = Stopwatch.StartNew();
while (sw.Elapsed < TimeSpan.FromSeconds(5))
{
    if (_repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id))
        break;
    await Task.Delay(100);
}
Assert.IsTrue(_repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id));
```

**Risk if unfixed:** Flaky failures in CI; 3s added to every suite run.

---

### 🔴 HIGH — Conditional Test Logic

**File:** `UserRepositoryIntegrationTests.cs` **Method:** `GetUser_ReturnsCorrectType` (lines 101-108)

```csharp
if (loaded is PremiumUser premium)
{
    Assert.IsTrue(premium.DiscountRate > 0);
}
else
{
    Assert.AreEqual("Eve", loaded!.Name);
}
```

**Problem:** One branch is never exercised (a `User("eve@example.com","Eve")` will always go to the `else` path). The `PremiumUser` assertion is dead code — you think you're testing it, but you never are.

**Fix:** Split into two explicit tests:
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void GetUser_StandardUser_ReturnsCorrectName()
{
    _repository.Insert(new User("eve@example.com", "Eve"));
    var loaded = _repository.GetByEmail("eve@example.com");
    Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
    Assert.AreEqual("Eve", loaded.Name);
}

[TestMethod]
public void GetUser_PremiumUser_HasDiscountRate()
{
    _repository.Insert(new PremiumUser("vip@example.com", "Vip", 0.15m));
    var loaded = _repository.GetByEmail("vip@example.com") as PremiumUser;
    Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
    Assert.IsTrue(loaded.DiscountRate > 0);
}
```

**Risk if unfixed:** Hidden testing gap — the `PremiumUser` branch is never reached, giving false confidence.

---

### 🔴 HIGH — Assertion-Free Test (a.k.a. Unknown Test)

**File:** `UserRepositoryIntegrationTests.cs` **Method:** `BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors` (lines 113-119)

```csharp
public void BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors()
{
    for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++)
    {
        _repository.Insert(new User($"bulk{i}@example.com", $"Bulk User {i}"));
    }
    // ← no assertion
}
```

**Calibration note:** The name `_RunsWithoutErrors` suggests a "does not throw" intent. MSTest will pass this as long as no exception is thrown — but it gives zero feedback if inserts silently fail (e.g., a no-op path or swallowed exception).

**Fix:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void BulkInsert_PersistsAllRecords()
{
    for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++)
    {
        _repository.Insert(new User($"bulk{i}@example.com", $"Bulk User {i}"));
    }

    var all = _repository.ListAll();
    Assert.AreEqual(100, all.Count);
}
```

**Risk if unfixed:** False pass — if `Insert` silently fails, this test still reports green.

---

### 🟡 MEDIUM — Assertion Roulette

**File:** `UserRepositoryIntegrationTests.cs` **Method:** `InsertUser_PersistsToDatabase` (lines 35-38)

```csharp
Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
Assert.AreEqual("Alice", loaded.Name);
Assert.AreEqual("alice@example.com", loaded.Email);
Assert.IsTrue(loaded.Id > 0);
```

Four assertions, none with a message. When one fails, the MSTest output shows only a line number — the developer must open the file to understand which property was wrong.

**Fix — add messages:**
```csharp
Assert.IsNotNull(loaded, "User should be retrievable after insert");
Assert.AreEqual("Alice", loaded.Name, "Name should round-trip");
Assert.AreEqual("alice@example.com", loaded.Email, "Email should round-trip");
Assert.IsTrue(loaded.Id > 0, "Auto-generated Id should be positive");
```

**Risk if unfixed:** Slower failure diagnosis, especially in CI logs.

---

## Smells Checked & Found Clean (15 of 19)

| Smell | Verdict | Notes |
|-------|---------|-------|
| Mystery Guest | ✅ Clean | In-memory SQLite — no external file/network dependency |
| Eager Test | ✅ Clean | No method calls 4+ distinct production methods; multi-call patterns appropriate for integration scope |
| Magic Number Test | ✅ Clean | `3` in `ListUsers` is contextually obvious (3 inserts immediately above); `10` in concurrency test likewise |
| Sensitive Equality | ✅ Clean | No `ToString()` in assertions |
| Exception Handling | ✅ Clean | No `try`/`catch` in tests |
| General Fixture | ✅ Clean | `_connection` and `_repository` are used by all 7 test methods |
| Ignored/Disabled Test | ✅ Clean | No skipped tests |
| Duplicate Assert | ✅ Clean | No duplicated assertions |
| Lazy Test | ✅ Clean | Shared helper calls (`Insert`, `GetByEmail`) are setup, not primary actions |
| Constructor Initialization | ✅ Clean | Uses `[TestInitialize]`, not a constructor |
| Default Test | ✅ Clean | Class name is descriptive |
| Redundant Print | ✅ Clean | No print/console statements |
| Redundant Assertion | ✅ Clean | No tautological assertions |
| Resource Optimism | ✅ Clean | In-memory SQLite, no assumed external files |
| Empty Test | ✅ Clean | No empty test bodies |

---

## Well-Written Tests Worth Noting

`DeleteUser_RemovesFromDatabase`, `UpdateUser_ModifiesExistingRecord`, and `InsertUser_ConcurrentInserts_MaintainsIntegrity` are clean — focused action, clear assertions, no smells. The concurrency test is a particularly good integration-level pattern.

---

## Prioritized Remediation Plan

| Priority | Smell | Test Method | Effort | Why First |
|----------|-------|-------------|--------|-----------|
| 1 | Conditional Test Logic | `GetUser_ReturnsCorrectType` | ~10 min | Dead branch = hidden gap; split into 2 tests |
| 2 | Assertion-Free Test | `BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors` | ~2 min | Add one assertion; prevents false-pass |
| 3 | Sleepy Test | `NotifyOnInsert_SendsEventAfterDelay` | ~10 min | Replace `Thread.Sleep` with polling loop |
| 4 | Assertion Roulette | `InsertUser_PersistsToDatabase` | ~2 min | Add message strings to existing asserts |

**Bottom line:** 4 of 8 tests have smells. The three High-severity findings (#1–#3) are the ones that actually hide bugs or cause flaky failures — fix those first. The Assertion Roulette is a readability improvement worth doing but lower urgency.
